<subSubSection pageNumber="481" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="481">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="481">Note:</emphasis>
Wijnands &amp; Belder (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="481">Misc. Pap. Landbouwhoogeschool</emphasis>
19: 429. 1980) state that the Boccone plate (1697: 108, t. 85), cited in synonymy, is not identifiable as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="481">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Digitalis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="thapsi">D. thapsi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Hinz (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="481">Candollea</emphasis>
42: 187. 1987) argued that both it and the cited Barrelier plate conflict with the diagnosis and designated a 
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
. However, cited plates form part of the protologue and cannot therefore be rejected as being in conflict with it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
